<s-topics>
<s-topic> quickSQL </s-topic>
</s-topics>
<s-title>
Quick SQL Execution
</s-title>
<s-description>
Simplifies queries by submitting an SQL command and fetching 
its output in one function
</s-description>
<s-usage>
<s-old-style-usage>
quickSQL(con, statement, ...)
</s-old-style-usage>
</s-usage>
<s-args-required>
<s-arg name= con >
an open <s-class>dbConnection</s-class> object.
</s-arg>
<s-arg name= statement >
an SQL statement as a character vector.
</s-arg>
</s-args-required>
<s-args-optional>
<s-arg name= ... >
any additional arguments specific to the database engine
may be specified.
</s-arg>
</s-args-optional>
<s-value>
a <s-function name = "data.frame">data.frame</s-function>
in the case of a <code>SELECT</code>-like statement, or
NULL otherwise.
</s-value>
<s-details>
This function simply calls <s-function name="dbExecStatement.sgm">
dbExecStatement</s-function> followed by
<s-function name="fetch.sgm">fetch</s-function>.
</s-details>
<s-section name = "BUGS:">
Perhaps this function should be named <code>dbQuery</code>
or <code>dbImmediate</code>?
